Enable editing files with syntax errors having a "%}" without matching "{%".

Example (it has a syntax error, but still it should allow to change "bar"):

%{ if flag?(:foo) %}
  bar
%{ end %}

add outline-regexp to allow for folding using outline-minor-mode

Emacs programming language modes outline-regexp to allow for folding and outlining of code. Since this feature is handy to have it is good to have this variable set. Especially for those that use outline-minor-mode frequently.
